# AlgoPay Figma Design Reference Rule

## Context
The Figma project "AlgoPay Frontend Design" is the single source of truth for all UI, components, colors, typography, spacing, and layout in this codebase. Algo Pay is a Philippine fintech with a dark theme and gold (#f0c050) accent.

## Required Behavior on Every Prompt

Before generating, modifying, or reviewing ANY UI code (components, pages, styles, layouts, Tailwind, JSX/TSX, CSS, design tokens), you MUST:

1. Query the Figma MCP first. Fetch the relevant frame, component, or token from "AlgoPay Frontend Design". Do not rely on memory or generic patterns.

2. Map the user's request to a specific Figma node. If they mention a screen or component name, search the Figma project for that exact name or closest match.

3. Extract concrete values — actual hex codes, font families, font sizes, line heights, paddings, margins, radii, shadows. Never approximate.

4. Start code output with a comment block listing the Figma nodes referenced, e.g.:
   // Figma ref: AlgoPay Frontend Design → Screens / Loan Investigator / Verdict Panel
   // Tokens: color/gold-accent (#f0c050), spacing/md (16px), radius/lg (12px)

5. If the Figma MCP fails or the node is missing, STOP and ask: "I could not find <node> in the AlgoPay Frontend Design Figma project. Can you confirm the frame name or paste a Figma link?" Do not silently fall back.

## When This Rule Does NOT Apply
- Pure backend, database, or API work with no UI surface
- Build config, tooling, CI, dependency updates
- Docs with no UI code

## Brand Constraints (always honor)
- Dark theme baseline
- Gold accent: #f0c050
- Philippine peso (₱) for currency
- Professional tone, light Filipino humor welcome in copy
- Mobile-responsive by default

## Output Discipline
- Match Figma pixel-for-pixel unless told otherwise
- Flag conflicts between existing code and Figma
- Prefer design tokens over hardcoded values
